  "text": "MicroRNAs (miRNAs) are a class of~22 nucleotides that are single strand non-coding RNAs that typically repress target genes at posttranscriptional level. A large number of studies have implicated miRNAs in almost all kinds of human cancers, and altered miRNA levels can result in aberrant expression of gene products that may contribute to cancer development [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
